    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <head>No. 478.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bátres</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 11,
                                1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have had the honor to receive your note
                            of the 24th ultimo, and have had a copy of it and other papers at the
                            Department, in relation to the schooner Ounalaska, forwarded to the
                            Attorney-General of the United States for such use as may be deemed
                            advisable in any prosecution against that vessel at San Francisco,
                            whither she has been dispatched, under guard, by the United States
                            minister to the Central American States, for having violated the
                            neutrality laws of this country.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ALVEY A. ADEE,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
